Medium-Sized South African House Prices Increase Average 5.2% in September

-- B y   G o r d o n   B e l l
-- 
2011-10-06T05:47:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-06/absa-says-s-africa-house-prices-rose-average-5-2-in-september.html
Absa Group Ltd. (ASA)  said the price of a
medium-sized house in  South Africa  rose an average 5.2 percent
in September froma year earlier.  The average nominal price of small houses fell 1.8 percent
and the price for large house increased by 0.5 percent, the
Johannesburg-based lender said in an e-mailed statement today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gordon Bell at 
 gbell16@bloomberg.net  